        "\n",
        "## How to Use Pointplank to Understand, Validate, and Document Your Data 路 [Rich Iannone, Software Engineer Posit]{style=\"color:#7F8A80;\"}\n",
        "\n",
        ":::::: columns\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"35%\"}\n",
        "![](images/pointblank.png){fig-align=\"center\" width=\"220\"}\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"65%\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "- Workshop Material: https://github.com/rich-iannone/pointblank-workshop\n",
        "- Package Documentation: https://rstudio.github.io/pointblank/\n",
        "\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::::::\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\\\n",
        "\n",
        "## Getting Startet with  LLM APIs in R 路 [Sara Altman, Data Science Educator Posit]{style=\"color:#7F8A80;\"}\n",
        "\n",
        ":::::: columns\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"60%\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "::: small-space\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "This workshop introduced the basics of working with large language models (LLMs) in R using the [{ellmer}](https://ellmer.tidyverse.org/) and [{shinychat}](https://posit-dev.github.io/shinychat/r/index.html) packages. Additionally it covered prompt engineering, tool calling, and practical applications of LLMs in R. See also Joe Chengs' workshop at the [R/ Medicine 2025](/blog/10_R_medicine_2025/) virtual conference.\n",
        "\n",
        "Most important learnings for me:\n",
        "\n",
        "* how to get structured outputs from unstructured content, such as text or images\n",
        "* difference between *system* and *user* prompts and how to set them using `{ellmer}`\n",
        "* system prompts can be saved in markdown files for reuse and contain dynamic content\n",
        "* concept of *tool calling* (illustration the right) to bring up-to-date information to LLMs (major limitation of LLMs!)\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"40%\"}\n",
        "![](images/tool_calling.png){fig-align=\"center\" width=\"450\"}\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::::::\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Find the workshop material [here](https://skaltman.github.io/r-pharma-llm/) and see the GitHub [repository](https://github.com/skaltman/r-pharma-llm) for demos and exercises.\n",
        "\n",
        "More material & R tools to interact with LLMs mentioned in the workshop:\n",
        "[Antropic's Prompt Engineering Overview](https://docs.claude.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering/overview);\n",
        "[OpenAI Cookbook](https://cookbook.openai.com/); \n",
